provide
			 consistent, reliable, and searchable Government-wide spending data that is
			 displayed accurately for taxpayers and policymakers on USASpending.gov;

analyze Federal
			 spending data to proactively prevent waste, fraud, abuse, and improper
			 payments;

specify such
				search shall be confined to Federal
				funds;

not less than once
				each quarter with information relating to Federal
				funds;

common data
				elements developed and maintained by accounting standards organizations;
				and

incorporate a
				widely accepted, nonproprietary, searchable, platform-independent
				computer-readable format;

request input from
				Federal award recipients to reduce duplicative financial reporting, especially
				from State and local governments and institutions of higher education;

other information
				maintained by Federal, State, local, and foreign government agencies;
				and

include recipients
			 that collectively receive not less than $1,000,000,000 in Federal funds each
			 fiscal year;

include recipients
			 that receive Federal funds under multiple programs across multiple agencies;
			 and

consolidating some
			 or all aspects of Federal financial reporting to reduce the costs to recipients
			 of Federal funds;
